@startuml User Journey
!theme plain

title PC Builder Platform - User Journey (Activity Diagram)

start

:User opens the platform;

:Configurator displays 7 component slots\n(CPU, Motherboard, GPU, RAM,\nStorage, PSU, Case);

repeat
  :User clicks a component category;
  :Platform fetches component list\nGET /api/components?category=<cat>;
  :User selects a component;
  :Platform calls POST /api/compatibility/validate;

  if (Compatibility errors?) then (yes)
    :Highlight incompatible components\nin red in Build Summary;
    :Display error alerts\n(socket_mismatch / ram_type_mismatch\n/ gpu_too_long);
  else (no)
    if (Compatibility warnings?) then (yes)
      :Display warnings\n(ram_frequency_exceeded\n/ psu_underpowered);
    endif
  endif

  :Update Build Summary:\n- Show selected component\n- Show total TDP\n- Show recommended PSU wattage;

repeat while (More components to select?) is (yes)
-> no;

:User clicks on a component\nto compare prices;

:Platform fetches\nGET /api/components/:id/prices;

:Display price offers sorted\nby ascending price:\n- Retailer name\n- Price (MAD)\n- Stock availability\n- Last updated date;

if (Offers available?) then (no)
  :Show "Not available from\nany referenced retailer";
  stop
endif

:User clicks on a retailer offer;

:Open retailer product page\nin a new browser tab;

:User completes purchase\non retailer's website;

stop

@enduml
